data.name: Tuesday Round-Up: Where does Russell Wilson rank according to NFL insiders?

data.message: No QB can carry a team week after week without much help....look at Drew Brees last season, and he's definitely Tier 1. Brady has done it occasionally but he still has Belichick and their offensive system. I think this criteria is a bait for people to say Wilson is Tier 2, ha

2: Russell is a great player, however, he can't do it all alone. If not for Marshawn's crazy run, Jermain's acrobatic catch and number 13's onside kick recovery, we wouldn't have even seen the Super Bowl last year! Again Russell is great at what he does, but he wouldn't have the same numbers/success if he played for, let's say the Cleveland Browns!

Russell Wilson is not an elite Quarterback. However, he is an excellent system Quaterback who is perfect for the Seattle Seahawk's game plan. In his first three seasons, he led his team to three playoff appearances, two Superbowls, and one Superbowl victory. The Seahawk organization would be crazy not to pay him according to his worth to the team.

People saying tier 3 üòÇüòÇüòÇüòÇ. Usually they have some solid wide outs to throw to.. Like Brady has always had a target to throw to, right now that's gronkowski, in the past in been Welker, Branch, Moss. So if you're trying to call Russ anything but tier one for that reason then Brady would be too. Bet you all would agree that Brady is tier one, Russ deserves to be in that category.

One player doesn't carry the entire team for the whole season. Look at the Raiders. Derek Carr is actually a pretty good QB, but he's not getting any help in Oakland. Drew Brees is definitely a Tier 1 QB, and the Saints were awful last season. Tom Brady can do it occasionally, but he also has a really good O-line and a smart head coach. Peyton Manning has had the help of being completely loaded at receiver. Aaron Rodgers, like Russell Wilson, has had the help of a talented running back. Unlike Wilson, however, he's also got several Pro Bowl receivers to throw the ball to. Tony Romo had the help of a great offensive line, a pretty good running back, and a great WR. And the quarterback has nothing to do with how the defense plays. The Saints had the number one offense last season, but if I remember correctly they ranked 31st in defense.
